description:
File: lichen/subsys/lichen/meshtastic/adapter.c:779-784

When portnum is MESHTASTIC_PORTNUM_ADMIN_APP, parse_admin_payload is called only if payload is not NULL:
  } else if (info->portnum == MESHTASTIC_PORTNUM_ADMIN_APP &&
             info->payload != NULL) {
      if (!parse_admin_payload(info->payload, info->payload_len, &info->kind)) {
          info->kind = LICHEN_MESHTASTIC_ADAPTER_PACKET_MALFORMED;
      }
  } else {
      info->kind = LICHEN_MESHTASTIC_ADAPTER_PACKET_UNSUPPORTED;
  }

If portnum is ADMIN_APP but payload is NULL, it falls through to UNSUPPORTED. This could mask a malformed packet (admin messages should have payloads).

Consider explicitly marking NULL-payload admin messages as MALFORMED for better diagnostics.
